title: Literary St. Petersburg : a guide to the city and its writers
creator: Blair, Elaine
subject1: Russian literature -- Russia (Federation) -- Saint Petersburg -- History and criticism
subject2: Authors, Russian -- Russia (Federation) -- Saint Petersburg -- Biography
description2: Alexander Pushkin -- Nikolai Gogol -- Ivan Turgenev -- Fydor Dostoevsky -- Leo Tolstoy -- Alexander Blok -- Andrei Bely -- Yevgeny Zamyatin -- Anna Akhmatova -- Osip Mandelstam -- Vladimir Mayakovsky -- Mikhail Zoschenko -- Vladimir Nabokov -- Daniil Kharms -- Joseph Brodsky.
description3: Much of Russian literature is St. Petersburg literature: set in the city, about the city, or written by writers living there. This unique guide profiles fifteen authors whose works and lives were intimately connected to this magnificent setting. Biographical sketches focus on the city as the writers knew it, a sense of their work, the literary and social circles in which they moved, and the sites associated with them. Travelers can wander through the museum where the teenage Vladimir Nabokov romanced his girlfriend and see the prison where Anna Akhmatova was inspired to write her epic poem about the Great Terror. They can find the statue that comes to life in Pushkinʼs poem The Bronze Horseman and visit the square where Crime and Punishmentʼs murderer/hero kneels on the ground to ask Godʼs forgiveness. Literary St. Petersburg opens the door to one of the most beautiful cities on earth and a body of literature that is as rich, subtle, and expressive as any in the world.

title: The patriarch and the tsar ..
creator: Palmer, William
description1: I. The replies of the humble Nicon, by the Mercy of God patriarch, against the questions of the boyar Simeon Streshneff and the answers of the metropolitan of Gaza, Paisius Ligarides.--II. Testimonies concerning the patriarch Nicon, the tsar, and the boyars, from the Travels of the patriarch Macarius of Antioch, written in Arabic by his son and archdeacon Paul of Aleppo.--III. History of the condemnation of the patriarch Nicon by a plenary council of the Orthodox Catholic eastern church, held at Moscow A. D. 1666-1667: written by Paisius Ligarides of Scio.--IV-VI. Services of the patriarch Nicon to the church and state of his country, and their requital by the creation of a merely national or state church in Russia; with some account of those punishments, personal and public, which were foretold by Nicon, and which have actually ensued.

description3: T. 1-2 . Povi︠e︡sti i rasskazy. -- t. 3. Zapiski iz mertvogo doma. Skvernyĭ anekdot. Zimnīi︠a︡ zametki o li︠e︡tnikh vpechatli︠e︡nīi︠a︡kh. Zapiski iz podpolʹi︠a︡. -- t. 4. Unizhennye i oskorblennye. Vi︠e︡chnyĭ muzh. -- t. 5. Prestupli︠e︡nīe i nakazanīe. -- t. 6. Idīot. -- t. 7. Bi︠e︡sy. -- t. 8. Podrostok. -- t. 9. Kriticheskīi︠a︡ statʹi. Dnvnik pisatelʹi︠a︡ za 1873 g. Politicheskīi︠a︡ statʹi. -- t. 10. Dnevnik pisateli︠a︡ za 1876 g. -- t. 11. Dnevnik pisateli︠a︡ za 1877 g. -- t. 12. Bratʹi︠a︡ Karamazovy.

title: Polnoe sobranīe sochinenīĭ
creator: Pushkin, Aleksandr Sergeevich
description2: Contents: 1. Liricheskīi︠a︡ stikhotvorenīi︠a︡ -- 2. Poėmy, skazki, Pi︠e︡sni zapadnykh slavi︠a︡n -- 3. Evgenīĭ Oni︠e︡gin i dramaticheskīi︠a︡ proizvedenīi︠a︡ -- 4. Romany, povi︠e︡sti, zapiski i zami︠e︡tki -- 5. Otryvki, povi︠e︡sti, razskazy i dramaticheskīi︠a︡ prozivedenīi︠a︡; zhurnalʹnyi︠a︡ i istoricheskīi︠a︡ statʹi -- 6. Istorīi︠a︡ Pugachevskago bunta.

title: Polnoe sobranīe sochinenīĭ
creator: Pushkin, Aleksandr Sergeevich
description2: Contents: 1. Liricheskīi︠a︡ stikhotvorenīi︠a︡ -- 2. Poėmy, skazki, Pi︠e︡sni zapadnykh slavi︠a︡n -- 3. Evgenīĭ Oni︠e︡gin i dramaticheskīi︠a︡ proizvedenīi︠a︡ -- 4. Romany, povi︠e︡sti, zapiski i zami︠e︡tki -- 5. Otryvki, povi︠e︡sti, razskazy i dramaticheskīi︠a︡ prozivedenīi︠a︡; zhurnalʹnyi︠a︡ i istoricheskīi︠a︡ statʹi -- 6. Istorīi︠a︡ Pugachevskago bunta.

title: Polnoe sobranie sochineniĭ : v desi͡ati tomakh
creator: Pushkin, Aleksandr Sergeevich
description1: At head of title: Akademii͡a nauk SSSR. Institut russkoĭ literatury (Pushkinskiĭ dom).
description2: t. 1. Stikhotvorenii͡a, 1813-1820.--t. 2. Stikhotvorenii͡a, 1820-1826.--t. 3. Stikhotvorenii͡a, 1827-1836.--t. 4. Poėmy. Skazki.--t. 5. Evgeniĭ Onegin. Dramaticheskie proizvedenii͡a.--t. 6. Khudozhestvennai͡a proza.--t. 7. Kritika i publit͡sistika.--t. 8. Avtobiograficheskai͡a i istoricheskai͡a proza. Istorii͡a pugacheva. Zapiski Moro-de-Braze.--t. 9. Istorii͡a Petra. Zametki o Kamchatke.--t. 10. Pisʹma.

title: Sochinenīi͡a A.S. Pushkina : s prilozhenīem snimka s pami͡atnika, vozdvignutago poėtu v Moskvi͡e v 1880 g
creator: Pushkin, Aleksandr Sergeevich
description1: The frontispiece of v. 1 and 6 are portraits, that of v. 7 a folded facsimile.
description2: 880-06"Bibliograficheskii͡a primi͡echanii͡a" at end of each volume.
description4: 880-07t. 1. Stikhotvorenii͡a 1811-1824 godov. Ruslan i Li͡udmila, Kavkazskiĭ pli͡ennik, Bratʹia razboĭnikhi, Bakhchisaraiskiĭ fontan, T͡Sygane [sic] -- t. 2. Stikhotvorenii͡a 1825-1830 godov. Boris Godunov. Nulin. Poltava. Galub. Domik v Kolomni͡e. Dramaticheskaii͡a proizvedenii͡a -- t. 3. Stikhotvorenīi͡a 1831-1836 godov. Evgenīĭ Oni͡egin. Skazki. Pi͡esni zapadnykh slavi͡an. Rusalka. Mi͡ednyĭ vsadnikh. Andzhelo -- t. 4. Romany, povi͡esti, otryki iz povi͡esteĭ i neokonchennye razskazy. (1827-1835) -- t. 5. Proza 1815-1837 godov. Kriticheskii͡a, bibliograficheskii͡a, polemicheskii͡a i istoricheskii͡a statʹi i zami͡etki. Dnevnik. Zapiski. Puteshestvie -- t. 6. Proza 1832-1836 godov. Istorii͡a pugachevskago bunta. Istoricheskie materialy -- t. 7. Pisʹma 1816-1837 godov.

title: Sochinenii͡a
creator: Turgenev, Ivan Sergeevich
description1: v.1 Stikhotvoreni͡a, poemy stat'i i ret͡senzii prozancheskie nabroski 1834-1849.--v.2 St͡seny i komedii 1843-1849.--v.3 St͡seny i komedii 1849-1852.--v.4 Zapiski okhotnika 1847-1874.--v.5 Povesti i Rasskazy. Stat'i i ret͡senzii 1844-1854.--v.6 Povesti i rasskazy "Rudin" stat'i i vospominanii͡a 1853-1856.--v.7 Povesti i rasskazy "Dvori͡anskoe gnēzdo" 1856-1858.--v.8 Nakanune, Gamlet i Don-Kikhot, ott͡sy i deti.--v.9 Povesti i rasskazy. "Dym" 1860-1867.--v.10 Povesti i rasskazy 1867-1870.--v.11 Povesti i rasskazy 1871-1877.--v.12 Nov' Predislovie k romanam.--v.13 Povesti, rasskazy, stikhotvorenii͡a v proze 1878-1883; Proiz rasmykh godov.--v.14 Vospominenii͡a kritika i publit͡sistika 1854-1883.--v.15 Korrespondent͡sii, rechi, predislovii͡a otkrytye pis'ma avtobinograficheskoe i prochee 1848-1883.

description1: "Krome obyknovennlykh ėkzempli︠a︡rov ėtogo izdanii︠a︡, napechatano sto desi︠a︡tʹ nomerovannykh roskoshnykh ėkzempli︠a︡rov: NoNo 1-10--Desi︠a︡t ėkzempli︠a︡rov na vatmanskoĭ bumage ... No 1 Ėkzempli︠a︡r Gennadii︠a︡ Vasilʹevicha I︠U︡dina."
description3: I. Liricheskii︠a︡ stikhotvorenii︠a︡ (1812-1824)--II. Liricheskii︠a︡ stikhotvorenii︠a︡ (1825-1836)  Poėmy (1820-1822)--III. Poėmy.  Dramaticheskii︠a︡ proizvedenii︠a︡.  Skazki (1823-1834)--IV. Evgenii Onegin (1822-1831)  Romany i povesti (1827-1833)--V. Povesti, st︠s︡eny, anekdoty (1834-1835)  Otryvki povesteĭ (1819-1835)  Arzrum (1829-1835)  Radishchev (1833-1836)  Zapiski.  Istoricheskii︠a︡ i kriticheskii︠a︡ zametki (1815-1835)--VI. Statʹi iz "Sovremennika" (1836-1837)  Istorii︠a︡ Pugachevskago bunta (1833-1834)  Kamchatka..  Petr Velikiĭ (1832-1837)--VII. Pisʹma A. S. Pushkina (1815-1837)--VIII. Primechanii︠a︡, dobavlenii︠a︡ i popravki.  S Prilozheniem dvukh snimkov s pocherka Pushkina.

title: A sportsman's sketches
creator: Turgenev, Ivan Sergeevich
description2: v. 1. Hor and Kalinitch. Yermolaï and the miller's wife. Raspberry spring. The district doctor. My neighbor Radilov. The peasant proprietor Ovsyanikov. Lgov. Byezhin prairie. Kassyan of Fair springs. The agent. The counting-house. Biryuk. Two country gentlemen. Lebedyan.- v. 2. Tatyana Borissovna and her nephew. Death. The singers. Piotr Petrovich Karataev. The tryst. The hamlet of the Shtchigri district. Tchertop-Hanov and Nedopyuskin. The end of Tchertop-Hanov. A living relic. The rattling of wheels. Epilogue: The forest and the steppe.
